cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper addresses action temporal localization in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a novel loss function, which involves optimization, and therefore, it could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
